42/* This code implements the Mersenne Twister pseudorandom number generator
43 by Takuji Nishimura and Makoto Matsumoto. The buffer initialization
44 function is different in order to permit seeds greater than 2^32-1.
45
46 This file contains a special __gmp_randinit_mt_noseed which excludes the
47 seeding function from the gmp_randfnptr_t routines. This is for use by
48 mpn_random and mpn_random2 on the global random generator. MT seeding
49 uses mpz functions, and we don't want mpn routines dragging mpz functions
50 into the link. */
51
52
53/* Default seed to use when the generator is not initialized. */
54#define DEFAULT_SEED 5489 /* was 4357 */
55
56/* Tempering masks. */
57#define MASK_1 0x9D2C5680
58#define MASK_2 0xEFC60000

169void
170__gmp_mt_recalc_buffer (gmp_uint_least32_t mt[])
171{
172 gmp_uint_least32_t y;
173 int kk;
174
175 for (kk = 0; kk < N - M; kk++)
176 {
177 y = (mt[kk] & 0x80000000) | (mt[kk + 1] & 0x7FFFFFFF);
178 mt[kk] = mt[kk + M] ^ (y >> 1) ^ ((y & 0x01) != 0 ? MATRIX_A : 0);
179 }
180 for (; kk < N - 1; kk++)
181 {
182 y = (mt[kk] & 0x80000000) | (mt[kk + 1] & 0x7FFFFFFF);
183 mt[kk] = mt[kk - (N - M)] ^ (y >> 1) ^ ((y & 0x01) != 0 ? MATRIX_A : 0);
184 }
185
186 y = (mt[N - 1] & 0x80000000) | (mt[0] & 0x7FFFFFFF);
187 mt[N - 1] = mt[M - 1] ^ (y >> 1) ^ ((y & 0x01) != 0 ? MATRIX_A : 0);
188}

191/* Get nbits bits of output from the generator into dest.
192 Note that Mersenne Twister is designed to produce outputs in
193 32-bit words. */
194void
195__gmp_randget_mt (gmp_randstate_t rstate, mp_ptr dest, unsigned long int nbits)
196{
197 gmp_uint_least32_t y;
198 int rbits;
199 mp_size_t i;
200 mp_size_t nlimbs;
201 int *pmti;
202 gmp_uint_least32_t *mt;
203
204 pmti = &((gmp_rand_mt_struct *) RNG_STATE (rstate))->mti;
205 mt = ((gmp_rand_mt_struct *) RNG_STATE (rstate))->mt;
206
207 nlimbs = nbits / GMP_NUMB_BITS;
208 rbits = nbits % GMP_NUMB_BITS;
209
210#define NEXT_RANDOM \
211 do \
212 { \
213 if (*pmti >= N) \
214 { \
215 __gmp_mt_recalc_buffer (mt); \
216 *pmti = 0; \
217 } \
218 y = mt[(*pmti)++]; \
219 y ^= (y >> 11); \
220 y ^= (y << 7) & MASK_1; \
221 y ^= (y << 15) & MASK_2; \
222 y ^= (y >> 18); \
223 } \
224 while (0)
225
226
227 /* Handle the common cases of 32- or 64-bit limbs with fast,
228 optimized routines, and the rest of cases with a general
229 routine. In all cases, no more than 31 bits are rejected
230 for the last limb so that every version of the code is
231 consistent with the others. */
232
233#if (GMP_NUMB_BITS == 32)
234
235 for (i = 0; i < nlimbs; i++)
236 {
237 NEXT_RANDOM;
238 dest[i] = (mp_limb_t) y;
239 }
240 if (rbits)
241 {
242 NEXT_RANDOM;
243 dest[nlimbs] = (mp_limb_t) (y & ~(ULONG_MAX << rbits));
244 }
245
246#else /* GMP_NUMB_BITS != 32 */
247#if (GMP_NUMB_BITS == 64)
248
249 for (i = 0; i < nlimbs; i++)
250 {
251 NEXT_RANDOM;
252 dest[i] = (mp_limb_t) y;
253 NEXT_RANDOM;
254 dest[i] |= (mp_limb_t) y << 32;
255 }
256 if (rbits)
257 {
258 if (rbits < 32)
259 {
260 NEXT_RANDOM;
261 dest[nlimbs] = (mp_limb_t) (y & ~(ULONG_MAX << rbits));
262 }
263 else
264 {
265 NEXT_RANDOM;
266 dest[nlimbs] = (mp_limb_t) y;
267 if (rbits > 32)
268 {
269 NEXT_RANDOM;
270 dest[nlimbs] |=
271 ((mp_limb_t) (y & ~(ULONG_MAX << (rbits-32)))) << 32;
272 }
273 }
274 }
275
276#else /* GMP_NUMB_BITS != 64 */
277
278 {
279 /* Fall back to a general algorithm. This algorithm works by
280 keeping a pool of up to 64 bits (2 outputs from MT) acting
281 as a shift register from which bits are consumed as needed.
282 Bits are consumed using the LSB bits of bitpool_l, and
283 inserted via bitpool_h and shifted to the right place. */
284
285 gmp_uint_least32_t bitpool_h = 0;
286 gmp_uint_least32_t bitpool_l = 0;
287 int bits_in_pool = 0; /* Holds number of valid bits in the pool. */
288 int bits_to_fill; /* Holds total number of bits to put in
289 destination. */
290 int bitidx; /* Holds the destination bit position. */
291 mp_size_t nlimbs2; /* Number of whole+partial limbs to fill. */
292
293 nlimbs2 = nlimbs + (rbits != 0);
294
295 for (i = 0; i < nlimbs2; i++)
296 {
297 bitidx = 0;
298 if (i < nlimbs)
299 bits_to_fill = GMP_NUMB_BITS;
300 else
301 bits_to_fill = rbits;
302
303 dest[i] = CNST_LIMB (0);
304 while (bits_to_fill >= 32) /* Process whole 32-bit blocks first. */
305 {
306 if (bits_in_pool < 32) /* Need more bits. */
307 {
308 /* 64-bit right shift. */
309 NEXT_RANDOM;
310 bitpool_h = y;
311 bitpool_l |= (bitpool_h << bits_in_pool) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
312 if (bits_in_pool == 0)
313 bitpool_h = 0;
314 else
315 bitpool_h >>= 32 - bits_in_pool;
316 bits_in_pool += 32; /* We've got 32 more bits. */
317 }
318
319 /* Fill a 32-bit chunk. */
320 dest[i] |= ((mp_limb_t) bitpool_l) << bitidx;
321 bitpool_l = bitpool_h;
322 bits_in_pool -= 32;
323 bits_to_fill -= 32;
324 bitidx += 32;
325 }
326
327 /* Cover the case where GMP_NUMB_BITS is not a multiple of 32. */
328 if (bits_to_fill != 0)
329 {
330 if (bits_in_pool < bits_to_fill)
331 {
332 NEXT_RANDOM;
333 bitpool_h = y;
334 bitpool_l |= (bitpool_h << bits_in_pool) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
335 if (bits_in_pool == 0)
336 bitpool_h = 0;
337 else
338 bitpool_h >>= 32 - bits_in_pool;
339 bits_in_pool += 32;
340 }
341
342 dest[i] |= (((mp_limb_t) bitpool_l
343 & ~(~CNST_LIMB (0) << bits_to_fill))
344 << bitidx);
345 bitpool_l = ((bitpool_l >> bits_to_fill)
346 | (bitpool_h << (32 - bits_to_fill))) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
347 bitpool_h >>= bits_to_fill;
348 bits_in_pool -= bits_to_fill;
349 }
350 }
351 }
352
353#endif /* GMP_NUMB_BITS != 64 */
354#endif /* GMP_NUMB_BITS != 32 */
355}

357void
358__gmp_randclear_mt (gmp_randstate_t rstate)
359{
360 (*__gmp_free_func) ((void *) RNG_STATE (rstate),
361 ALLOC (rstate->_mp_seed) * GMP_LIMB_BYTES);
362}
363
364void __gmp_randiset_mt (gmp_randstate_ptr, gmp_randstate_srcptr);
365
366static const gmp_randfnptr_t Mersenne_Twister_Generator_Noseed = {
367 NULL,
368 __gmp_randget_mt,
369 __gmp_randclear_mt,
370 __gmp_randiset_mt
371};
372
373void
374__gmp_randiset_mt (gmp_randstate_ptr dst, gmp_randstate_srcptr src)
375{
376 const mp_size_t sz = ((sizeof (gmp_rand_mt_struct) - 1) / GMP_LIMB_BYTES) + 1;
377 gmp_rand_mt_struct *dstp, *srcp;
378 mp_size_t i;
379
380 /* Set the generator functions. */
381 RNG_FNPTR (dst) = (void *) &Mersenne_Twister_Generator_Noseed;
382
383 /* Allocate the MT-specific state. */
384 dstp = (gmp_rand_mt_struct *) __GMP_ALLOCATE_FUNC_LIMBS (sz);
385 RNG_STATE (dst) = (mp_ptr) dstp;
386 ALLOC (dst->_mp_seed) = sz; /* Initialize alloc field to placate Camm. */
387
388 /* Copy state. */
389 srcp = (gmp_rand_mt_struct *) RNG_STATE (src);
390 for (i = 0; i < N; i++)
391 dstp->mt[i] = srcp->mt[i];
392
393 dstp->mti = srcp->mti;
394}
395
396void
397__gmp_randinit_mt_noseed (gmp_randstate_ptr dst)
398{
399 const mp_size_t sz = ((sizeof (gmp_rand_mt_struct) - 1) / GMP_LIMB_BYTES) + 1;
400 gmp_rand_mt_struct *dstp;
401 mp_size_t i;
402
403 /* Set the generator functions. */
404 RNG_FNPTR (dst) = (void *) &Mersenne_Twister_Generator_Noseed;
405
406 /* Allocate the MT-specific state. */
407 dstp = (gmp_rand_mt_struct *) __GMP_ALLOCATE_FUNC_LIMBS (sz);
408 RNG_STATE (dst) = (mp_ptr) dstp;
409 ALLOC (dst->_mp_seed) = sz; /* Initialize alloc field to placate Camm. */
410
411 /* Set state for default seed. */
412 for (i = 0; i < N; i++)
413 dstp->mt[i] = default_state[i];
414
415 dstp->mti = WARM_UP % N;
416}
